<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Boundless" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Boundless,</orth> unconfined, unbridled: <cit><quote>thy b. flood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 653" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 653</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. sea,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 65.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 65, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>beyond the infinite and b. reach of mercy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.117" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 117</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the desire is b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as b. as the sea,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 133</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. theft in limited professions,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.430" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 430</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. intemperance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. happiness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 24</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>